com.safenetinc.luna

Class LunaAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.safenetinc.luna.LunaAPI

  • public class LunaAPI
extends Object
    This class defines the JNI interface to the LunaAPI native library that is used to connect the JVM to the PKCS#11 cryptoki library.

    In general these methods are intended only for use only by SafeNet defined classes. These methods may change at any time and you are encouraged to make use of other interfaces. If you find you absolutely need to use a method here then request that method be wrapped via another more appropriate proprietary class like, say, LunaSLotManager, or LunaTokenObject.

        public int CheckSessionState(int sessionHandle)
                      throws LunaException
        Returns the PKCS11 state of the session. This is defined as:
        • 0 - read-only public session (full access to public session objects, read only access to public token objects)
        • 1 - read-only user session (full access to all session objects, read-only access to all token objects)
